description: The Jongmyo Shrine is a place dedicated to the Korean kings and kings. Because it preserves the ancient traditions and customs of solemn ceremonies, rituals and rituals, it is designated as a world cultural heritage. Visitors who love history must visit the four major palaces of Korea, the Jongmyo Temple and even the Tomb of the Joseon. It is a good way to understand the local culture.
ChanguimunGate (JahamunGate) is located in Seoul, also known as North Gate. It was built in 1396. The upper wooden gate was burned down and then rebuilt. This gate is the oldest of the four gates.
